  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to characterize Kupffer cell activity and activation of the innate
      immune response in the early phase of liver regeneration after right hepatectomy. The
      investigators hypothesise that liver regeneration after right hepatectomy in humans is
      associated with Kupffer cell activation and initiation of the innate immune response and that
      impaired liver regeneration, liver failure and sepsis following liver resection are
      associated with Kupffer cell dysfunction and an impaired innate immune response. The
      objectives for this study are to characterise Kupffer cell activity and the innate immune
      response in human liver before and after right hepatectomy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
